Package: rTAGS
Type: Package
Title: An R package for easy collection and powerful analysis of Twitter data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: K. Bret Staudt Willet, Joshua M. Rosenberg, Spencer P. Greenhalgh
Maintainer: K. Bret Staudt Willet <bret@bretsw.com>
Description: The goal of rTAGS is to sync together (a) the ease of collecting tweets over time with a **Twitter Archiving Google Sheet** [TAGS](https://tags.hawksey.info/), (b) the utility of the **rtweet** [package](https://rtweet.info/) for processing and preparing additional Twitter metadata, and (c) a collection of different analytic functions we have developed during our own social media research.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: 
        R (>= 3.1.0),
        dplyr,
        googlesheets,
        longurl,
        mapsapi,
        purrr,
        rtweet,
        stringr,
        tidyr,
        tidyselect,
        tidytext
        urltools,
        usethis
Suggests:
        ggplot2,
        knitr,
        rmarkdown,
        tidyverse
LazyData: TRUE
URL: https://github.com/bretsw/rtags
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
